// Search 01 — first real run of the Phase 6.5 evolutionary loop
// (Q-2026-07-13-C). Probes the chains/sieve neighborhood: the two cheap
// bonded regimes with opposite characters (chains: sparse eternal springs;
// sieve: information-gated survival/reproduction). Bands is deliberately
// absent — a bands-class screen costs ~16 min (108 min at 20k ticks,
// baseline finding 5), which would eat the whole budget.
//
// Budget shape: 2 seeds + 5 generations x 8 children = 42 screens at 3k
// ticks (a sieve-class screen costs ~50 s, a chains-class ~10 s); top 2
// confirmed at 6000 ticks — twice the screen horizon, to catch slow
// developers the screen mis-ranks. The corpus-horizon (20k) comparison of
// the champion happens per champion via `genesis score`, outside the
// search: a sieve-class 20k run costs an hour-plus and must be resumable.
//
// Reproduce with:
//   genesis search --spec sweeps/search-01.ron --out <dir>
// Committed results: docs/research/sweeps/2026-07-13-search-01/
(
    seed: 20260713,
    generations: 5,
    population: 8,
    survivors: 3,
    sigma: 0.3,
    screen_ticks: 3000,
    every: 100,
    confirm_ticks: Some(6000),
    confirm_top: 2,
    // Bounds a runaway-bonding mutant's evaluation cost (deterministically:
    // bond count is simulated state). ~10x the bond count a healthy
    // sieve-class screen reaches; a mutant condensing toward the
    // actual/bands regime (1-2M bonds at 20k) trips it long before it can
    // dominate a generation's wall time.
    bond_cap: Some(200000),
    seeds: [
        (
            name: "chains",
            rules: "packs/chains.ron",
        ),
        (
            name: "sieve",
            config: Some("configs/sieve.ron"),
            rules: "packs/sieve.ron",
        ),
    ],
)
